objectDesc.p: Papyrus, 26.3x14.2, 1 extant leaf(s), 1 column(s), 22 (?) line(s) per column, 22-24 characters per line, written in Greek.

history.provenance: Discovered by Ieras Monēs Theobadistou Orous Sina, Agias Aikaterinēs (Holy Monastery of St. Catherine at Mount Sinai) at Dayr al Qiddīsah Kātrīnā, Miṣr.
Transferred to Uspensky private collection at Ukraina, Kiev.
Transferred 1887-1889 to 152b, Geistliche Akademie, Archaologisches Museum at Ukraina, Kiev.
Transferred post 1954 to Natsionalʹna Biblioteka Ukraini imeni V. I. Vernadsʹkogo (Vernadsky National Library of Ukraine) at Ukraina, Kiev.

msIdentifier.msName: Petrov 533b, Natsionalʹna Biblioteka Ukraini imeni V. I. Vernadsʹkogo (Vernadsky National Library of Ukraine), Ukraina, Kiev.
